<h1>Tutorial 5. Assembling the Front of the Skirt.</h1>
<p><strong>I will use bone casing tape for further work. It is normally used with bra underwires. </strong>I chose this particular bone casing tape because it is robust and non-stretch. You can use almost any ribbon though: for example, some not too wide petersham ribbon as long as it is non-stretch, thick, and robust enough. Satin and even nylon ribbon can also do if you have no choice.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I take the petticoat off the dress-form. Please remember </strong>that there are stitched guidelines for putting gores on the petticoat.</p>
<p><strong>I have left some room for the train left and right of the central back seam at the back of the petticoat. The gores will go from either side of the train. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I measure a piece of bone casing tape of the same length as the bottom hoop of the petticoat. I start from the centre of the back, </strong>go around the perimeter, and trim the tape leaving a small overlap tail.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>What I have is a piece of bone casing tape which is a little longer than the bottom petticoat hoop. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image012.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>The end of the tape is supposed to be pinned to the gore guideline which borders with the train area. I leave a small overlap tail and mark the level of the guideline on the tape. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image014.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image016.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image018.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I bring the tape to the side seam without pulling it too tight. It is where the back gore stops and the first front gore begins. I secure the tape with a pin and mark the level of the side seam on it. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image020.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image022.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Let us continue. I bring the tape to the next stitched guideline without pulling it too tight, secure it with a pin, and mark another reference point on the tape. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image024.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image026.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I go past the other side seam and secure the tape at the last guideline marking another point on it. </strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image028.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I make sure the tape is distributed evenly along the bottom hoop and forms a ring. </strong>I pin down the ends to prevent them from flapping around.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image030.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>The same is done with the second hoop: I measure a piece of bone casing tape slightly longer than the hoop itself, pin it down at the gore guidelines, and make corresponding marks on the tape. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image032.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image034.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image036.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image038.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image040.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image042.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I have distributed the tape along the second petticoat hoop and marked the levels of all gore guidelines on it. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image044.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>The same thing needs to be done with the third hoop, too. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image046.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image048.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image050.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I have secured bone casing tapes along all three petticoat hoops and made relevant marks on them. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image052.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I think it is a good idea to put another tape on the petticoat 10cm above the third hoop and make the same kind of marks on it. </strong>It will go 60cm above the bottom edge of the petticoat on the actual garment, i.e. at about the knee level.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image054.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I measure 10cm along each gore guideline to mark the level of this additional tape.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image056.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image058.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Then, I measure a piece of bone casing tape equal to the circumference of the petticoat measured 10cm above the third hoop and put it down as marked.</strong> I leave a small overlap tail, as always.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image060.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I secure the tape at all gore guidelines and make corresponding marks on it like before. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image062.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image064.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image066.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image068.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>So, there is bone casing tape at four different levels of the petticoat: along the three hoops and 10cm above the third hoop. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image070.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>And now, starting from the train line, I need to pin the assembled gores to the bone casing tapes aligning their seam allowances with the marks on the tapes. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image072.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>The first thing I do is mark three sections at 10cm intervals along the seam allowances of the gores to align them with the marks on the tapes. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image074.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image076.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image078.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image080.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image082.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I make such marks on all seams joining the gores.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image084.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I unpin the top tape with marks on it. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image086.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I put the assembled gores wrong side up and align the first mark on the tape with the mark on the seam allowance for attaching the train. The bottom edge of the tape is aligned with the mark on the seam allowance of the gores. I pin the tape to the seam allowance. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image088.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I find the next mark on the tape and align it with the seam joining the first and the second gore. The bottom edge of the tape goes along the horizontal guideline. I pin the tape to the seam allowance. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image090.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image092.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I continue moving further and pinning the tape to the seam allowances of the gores.</strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image094.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image096.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image098.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I am sure you have already got the point. All our gores acquire the desired shape and volume, and they are also precise in size because all measurements were taken off the petticoat. </strong>Remember to serge the raw edges of the vertical joining seams on the full-size skirt.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image100.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image102.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I have distributed the top tape across the joined gores.</strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image104.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I unpin the tape going along the third hoop of the petticoat. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image106.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>And I distribute it and pin it down at the level of the third hoop the same way as described before.</strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image108.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image110.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image112.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>The second tape from the top now holds in place properly.</strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image114.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I move to the second hoop and do the same thing.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image116.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image118.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image120.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>It is time to unpin the tape going along the bottom hoop and distribute it across the joined gores.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image122.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image124.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image126.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image128.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image130.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Look what a beauty these gores are! </strong></p>
<p>You already know what to do if you need to add another tape closer to the top to make the folds hold better.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image132.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image134.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image136.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Here is our petticoat. </strong></p>
<p><strong>As for me, I think it looks very neat and pretty! </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%205.files/image138.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I put a measuring tape down under the petticoat. The diameter is about 65cm, which means it will be about 170cm on the actual skirt. </strong></p>
<p><strong>It is quite possible that it will reach up to 180cm with the face layer included. </strong></p>
<p>And this is what we wanted, this beautiful fullness!</p>
<p><strong>This stage is finished, and we can now move to the train area. </strong></p>

